Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
All parameters are within normal limits except for markedly elevated creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, and a mildly increased platelet distribution width, which may suggest platelet size variability. Renal function should be urgently evaluated and correlated clinically. All other hematological and biochemical values are unremarkable.
